<div class="gpp-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-7">
        <h2></h2>
        
            <div class="gen-group">
              
              <div class="gen-group__content">
                <p class="subheading">Site managed by</p>
                <h2>Ellergreen Hydro Ltd</h2>
              </div>
            </div>
        
        <div class="gen-content">
          <p>Scandale Hydro harnesses the heavy rainfall of the Lake District to generate zero carbon electricity for a significant proportion of its locality, which includes the town of Ambleside.</p>
<p>With a catchment area of 4.8km2, over 200m of fall along the 2.1km buried pipeline provide up to 900kW of power. It is the largest hydro generator in the Lake District, and one of the biggest river hydro schemes in England.</p>
<p>The Lake District is famed for its rainfall and beautiful mountainous scenery, making it ideal for hydro schemes, which can be built with minimal impact on the landscape. The scheme is expected to run for the next 50-100 years.</p>
<p>Revenue generated from export electricity provides income to local farmers and land managers as well as the investors who have backed the project.  These are all local to the scheme and include the UK’s oldest and leading hydro company Gilkes as well as the Diocese of Carlisle.  The Diocese is responsible for 351 churches and 105 schools, and also operates a newly built 500kW scheme at Rydal Hall.  This was also jointly developed with local company Ellergreen Hydro. </p>
<p>Scandale Hydro is one of the single largest contributors to the Lake District National Park’s Low Carbon vision for the area, which is aiming to cut the area’s carbon footprint year on year.</p>
          <p class="read-more"><a href="#" class="button">Read More</a></p>
        </div>
        

